.TH smi-full-update "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Base Command"
.SH NAME
smi-full-update \- Perform a full system and SMI environment update
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-full-update
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-full-update
is a high-level utility that orchestrates multiple update tasks. It ensures that the host operating system, and all managed environments (like jails), are brought up to date.
.PP
The script performs the following actions:
.IP 1.
Ensures it is running as root (re-executes with \fBsudo -i\fR if necessary).
.IP 2.
Executes \fBsmi-host-update\fR to update the host system.
.IP 3.
Executes \fBsmi-jails-update\fR to update all configured FreeBSD jails.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Imre Tabur.
.SH "REPORTING BUGS"
.PP
Report smi-full-update bugs to \fIinfo@setmy.info\fR
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR smi-host-update (1),
.BR smi-jails-update (1)

